# TypeScript & components (Pulse UI)

When editing `.ts` or `.tsx` in pulse-ui:

## TypeScript

- **No `any`** – use proper types; for errors use `unknown` or type guards. (P0.)
- **Constants** – prefer named constants/enums for domain values and magic numbers; local one-offs are OK.
- **Nullish coalescing** – use `??` for defaults, not `||`.
- **Types** – prefer `*.interface.ts` **in the feature (or component)** for that feature’s types; inline for local-only props. Use `src/types/` only for types shared across multiple features.

## Components

- **Clean JSX** – no business logic in JSX; put logic in custom hooks and pass handlers/derived values as props.
- **One component per file**; export from `index.ts` where used.
- **Props** – destructure in the function signature.
- **Hooks** – custom hooks in separate files (e.g. `hooks/useX.ts`), not inside component files.

## File naming

- Components: `PascalCase.tsx`. Types/constants: `FeatureName.interface.ts`, `FeatureName.constants.ts` (or under `src/constants/`).
